				<td colspan="2"><span>In big guilds where raids have 10+ groups and very defined bard roles, I can see some of the arguments that bards can just not be grouped with pullers.  But the fact is, bards are ideally suited to be tagging behind monks on pulls.  Want to split the two the monk split off the crowd?  Bard floating up behind with lull and Bellow is a perfect answer.  If a monk needs a tag NOW and not 3 seconds from now, a bard makes a great tagger.  I really like the speed and flexibility you get grouping a bard as tagger behind a monk.  But one of the keys to doing that job is knowing when to turn off songs.</span></td>
